.\" Manpage for opensplat. Generated from man/opensplat.1.in by CMake
.\" (version substituted at configure time). Edit the .in, not the build output.
.TH OPENSPLAT 1 "June 2026" "OpenSplat @OPENSPLAT_MAN_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
opensplat \- generate a 3D Gaussian Splatting scene from a photogrammetry project
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B opensplat
.RI [ project-path ]
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B opensplat
takes camera poses and sparse points from a
.BR COLMAP ,
.BR OpenSfM ,
.BR ODM ,
.B OpenMVG
or
.B nerfstudio
project and trains a 3D Gaussian Splatting model, writing a
.B .ply
or
.B .splat
scene file (plus a
.B cameras.json
alongside it).
.PP
The
.I project-path
must contain sparse points; random initialization is not supported. The
project format is auto-detected from its layout (e.g. a
.B sparse/
directory or
.B cameras.bin
for COLMAP, a
.B transforms.json
for nerfstudio).
.PP
On NVIDIA (CUDA), AMD (HIP/ROCm) and Apple (Metal) GPUs training runs on the
GPU; otherwise it falls back to the CPU (roughly 100x slower). The backend in
use is printed at startup ("Using CUDA" / "Using MPS" / "Using CPU").
.SH RESOURCE-AWARE PROCESS CONTRACT
On startup
.B opensplat
detects host RAM, GPU VRAM, CPU cores and the scene size, then resolves a
.I process contract
\(em a policy that selects the host image store, a hard cap on the gaussian
count (to bound VRAM), and, if necessary, an image downscale. The resolved
contract is printed before training. Every decision can be overridden; the
precedence, highest first, is:
.IP 1. 4
Command-line flags (e.g.
.BR --max-splats ).
.IP 2. 4
Environment variables (the
.B OPENSPLAT_*
variables; see
.BR ENVIRONMENT ).
.IP 3. 4
A JSON contract file given with
.BR --contract .
.IP 4. 4
A named profile given with
.BR --profile .
.IP 5. 4
Auto-detection from the detected hardware.
.PP
The named profiles are
.BR 2gb ", " 4gb ", " 6gb ", " 8gb " (set the host RAM budget in GiB) and "
.B full-throttle
(remove all caps, keep the fastest paths). Use
.B auto
(the default) to size everything from the detected machine.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Input / output
.TP
.BI \-i ", " \-\-input " path"
Path to the project (also accepted as the first positional argument).
.TP
.BI \-o ", " \-\-output " path"
Output scene file. A
.B .ply
or
.B .splat
extension selects the format. Default:
.BR splat.ply .
.TP
.BI \-s ", " \-\-save\-every " n"
Save the scene every
.I n
steps. \-1 disables intermediate saves. Default: \-1.
.TP
.BI \-\-resume " file.ply"
Resume training from a previously saved PLY.
.TP
.BI \-\-colmap\-image\-path " path"
Override the default image directory for COLMAP input.
.SS Validation
.TP
.B \-\-val
Withhold one camera and report its loss after training.
.TP
.BI \-\-val\-image " name"
Filename of the image to withhold. Default:
.BR random .
.TP
.BI \-\-val\-render " dir"
Render the validation view every 10 steps into
.IR dir .
.TP
.B \-\-keep\-crs
Retain the input project's coordinate reference system in the output.
.SS Compute backend
.TP
.B \-\-cpu
Force CPU execution even if a GPU is available.
.SS Resource contract (override the auto-detected policy)
.TP
.BI \-\-profile " name"
Resource profile:
.BR auto ", " 2gb ", " 4gb ", " 6gb ", " 8gb " or " full\-throttle .
Default:
.BR auto .
.TP
.BI \-\-contract " file.json"
Path to a JSON contract file (see
.BR "CONTRACT FILE" ).
.TP
.BI \-\-ram\-budget\-mb " mb"
Host RAM budget in MB. 0 = auto-detect.
.TP
.BI \-\-vram\-budget\-mb " mb"
GPU VRAM budget in MB. 0 = auto-detect.
.TP
.BI \-\-max\-splats " n"
Hard cap on the gaussian count to bound VRAM. 0 = unbounded. When auto, the cap
is derived from the VRAM budget (roughly 2000 bytes per gaussian, with 15%
headroom). Growth pauses at the first refinement past the cap; culling
continues.
.TP
.BI \-\-image\-store " mode"
Host image store:
.BR auto ", " f32 " or " u8 .
The
.B u8
store uses ~4x less host RAM and is bit-identical to
.B f32
(source images are 8-bit), at a small per-iteration conversion cost. Default:
.B auto
(picks
.B u8
when
.B f32
would not fit the RAM budget).
.TP
.BI \-\-min\-render\-px " px"
Warn if the rendered image's long side falls below
.I px
(a quality guard \(em over-downscaling small images destabilizes training).
Default: 400.
.SS Training schedule
.TP
.BI \-n ", " \-\-num\-iters " n"
Number of training iterations. Default: 30000.
.TP
.BI \-d ", " \-\-downscale\-factor " f"
Scale input images down by this factor before training. Default: 1.
.TP
.BI \-\-num\-downscales " n"
Number of progressive downscales; resolution doubles every
.B \-\-resolution\-schedule
steps. Default: 2.
.TP
.BI \-\-resolution\-schedule " n"
Double the working resolution every
.I n
steps. Default: 3000.
.TP
.BI \-\-sh\-degree " n"
Maximum spherical-harmonics degree (view-dependent color). Lower degrees use
less memory. Default: 3.
.TP
.BI \-\-sh\-degree\-interval " n"
Raise the active SH degree every
.I n
steps, up to
.BR \-\-sh\-degree .
Default: 1000.
.TP
.BI \-\-ssim\-weight " w"
Weight of the SSIM term in the loss (0 = L1 only). Default: 0.2.
.SS Densification
.TP
.BI \-\-refine\-every " n"
Split / duplicate / prune gaussians every
.I n
steps. Default: 100.
.TP
.BI \-\-warmup\-length " n"
Begin refinement only after
.I n
steps. Default: 500.
.TP
.BI \-\-reset\-alpha\-every " n"
Reset gaussian opacities every
.I n
refinements. Default: 30.
.TP
.BI \-\-densify\-grad\-thresh " x"
Positional-gradient threshold above which a gaussian is split/duplicated.
Default: 0.0002.
.TP
.BI \-\-densify\-size\-thresh " x"
Gaussians smaller than this are duplicated; larger ones are split. Default: 0.01.
.TP
.BI \-\-stop\-screen\-size\-at " n"
Stop splitting on screen-space size after
.I n
steps. Default: 4000.
.TP
.BI \-\-split\-screen\-size " x"
Split gaussians larger than this fraction of the screen. Default: 0.05.
.SS Information
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print usage and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.SH CONTRACT FILE
The file given to
.B \-\-contract
is JSON. Any subset of these keys may be set; unset keys fall through to the
profile / auto-detection:
.PP
.nf
.RS
{
  "profile":          "4gb",
  "ram_budget_mb":    4096,
  "vram_budget_mb":   4096,
  "max_gaussians":    1500000,
  "image_store":      "u8",
  "min_render_px":    400,
  "downscale_factor": 2
}
.RE
.fi
.SH ENVIRONMENT
These override the JSON contract and the profile, but not command-line flags:
.TP
.B OPENSPLAT_PROFILE
Same values as
.BR \-\-profile .
.TP
.B OPENSPLAT_RAM_BUDGET_MB
Host RAM budget in MB.
.TP
.B OPENSPLAT_VRAM_BUDGET_MB
GPU VRAM budget in MB.
.TP
.B OPENSPLAT_MAX_SPLATS
Hard gaussian cap.
.TP
.B OPENSPLAT_IMAGE_STORE
.BR auto ", " f32 " or " u8 .
.TP
.B OPENSPLAT_MIN_RENDER_PX
Minimum render long-side guard.
.TP
.B OPENSPLAT_DOWNSCALE_FACTOR
Image downscale factor.
.TP
.B OPENSPLAT_CONTRACT
Path to a JSON contract file (same as
.BR \-\-contract ).
.SH EXAMPLES
Train a scene with default settings:
.PP
.RS
.B opensplat /path/to/banana \-n 2000
.RE
.PP
Train on a low-RAM machine, capping VRAM, writing a compressed splat:
.PP
.RS
.B opensplat /path/to/scene \-\-profile 4gb \-\-max\-splats 1000000 \-o out.splat
.RE
.PP
Force the uint8 image store and a quality floor via environment:
.PP
.RS
.B OPENSPLAT_IMAGE_STORE=u8 OPENSPLAT_MIN_RENDER_PX=500 opensplat /path/to/scene
.RE
.PP
Pin a full policy from a file:
.PP
.RS
.B opensplat /path/to/scene \-\-contract contract.json
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B opensplat
exits 0 on success and non-zero on error (invalid arguments, an unreadable
project, or a training failure such as an out-of-memory condition).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I splat.ply
Default output scene (overridable with
.BR \-o ).
.TP
.I cameras.json
Camera set, written next to the output scene.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project documentation under
.IR docs/ ,
and the README. Online: <https://github.com/pierotofy/OpenSplat>.
.SH AUTHORS
OpenSplat is free software licensed under the AGPLv3. The methods are based on
nerfstudio's splatfacto.
